nsitive engagement with the families that make up these communities uncovers the complex interplay between loneliness and a host of economic and environmental practices, including the widespread local tradition of hunting. Wandering Spirits offers a vivid portrait of a largely overlooked world, in all its fragility and nuance, while engaging with core anthropological concerns of kinship and the structure of social relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aInterpersonal relationszGreenland. 0aInuitxKinshipzGreenlandxPsychological aspects. 0aInuitzGreenlandxSocial conditions. 0aKinshipzGreenlandxPsychological aspects. 0aLonelinessxSocial aspectszGreenland. 0aLonelinesszGreenland. 0aSocial isolationzGreenland. 0aSuicidezGreenland. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aGreenland.  aInuit.  akinship.  aloneliness.  alonging.  anaming.  apersonal autonomy.  apersonhood.  areincarnation.  asuicide.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107119430 cprintz978022661042940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226610733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226610733/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of